arChildNodes.szComment:
Donan rises to his feet and makes his way to the alchemical bench. 
The Player brings the materials they've been calibrating to Donan's side. 
In front of Donan, in the center of everything, is the Soulstone. It sits on a pedestal, secured in a gem-setting. 
It is dim, its heart nearly black, broken, and inactive.

There is a CRACK in the middle of the Soulstone.
He pours something out of a beaker: the 'soul soup' of hell. 
HORADRIC CHANTING echoes in the background as the Soulstone begins to glow and the soul soup darkens.
Donan stokes the fire beneath the workstation.

The Player sets a small mallet down next to him. Taissa and The Player stand behind Donan, watching him as he works. 
Their faces are lit by the flickering multicolored glow of the Soulstone.
Taissa lifts a flask and pours it over the Soulstone. The stone reacts and STEAM or SMOKE pours out from it. We hear a hiss.

Donan lifts the mallet higher than he has until now and strikes down with great force. 
The glow of the Stone is now constant, a clear amber, and unbroken.
Chant: "Chyha chyhichylú tnilm úchylumun, phantes a ichyhith." See Voice Direction for pronunciation

Donan strikes the Soulstone a second time.
Chant: "Chyha chyhichylú tnilm úchylumun, antud a thúrthi." See Voice Direction for pronunciation.
Donan strikes the Soulstone a third time.
Chant: "Chyha chyhichylú tnilm úchylumun, chyolors li sam thir nit eúchyhed."  See Voice Direction for pronunciation.

We hear the sound of something shattering and the glow intensifies suddenly, then dies away.
The stone itself now maintains a constant amber glow. It is active. Mended. 
Donan rises to his feet, Soulstone in hand. He appears both grim and reflective.
This breaks some of Donan's calm.
Donan glowers at her. Before he can speak, the Player intervenes, coming to stand between them.
